  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with a higher breast cancer risk (higher than 17% according to the IBIS calculation)
      will receive a 2D digital mammography together with a 3D tomosynthesis (so called combo tomo)
      of both breasts in two views in order to investigate the additional value of tomosynthesis in
      the diagnosis of breast cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
